During our two weeks in France we wanted to worship at a local church. We were very welcomed to this English speaking liturgical church. We went to the early 9am traditional service and enjoyed the organ and short message. Following there was a coffee time and we enjoyed chatting with other regulars and visitors.
We visited the evening service during a holiday. Very welcoming church! We found the pastors to be faithful and the congregation is lively and hungry for God's word.

This is a wonderful church where there is a very welcoming atmosphere. There are two morning services on a Sunday. A traditional service at 9.00. Followed by modern service at 10.45. Coffee and cakes are served at the end of the first service, which gives people an opportunity to meet and chat. The church has a very good choir. There are also different activities during the week.

You arrive at SMP and you know that you have reached your destination. Always √† warm welcome, √† lovely smile; child friendly environment and people to hang out with. Excellent space to commune with God and meet people of your Faith!
Great Church. Faithful pastors, faithful to the word, all walks of life worship there and very friendly. Good to see a church that is faithful.
Friendly, authentic church. Not a show. People engaging with their God, and open to people joining them. Last Sunday was great.
Best English speaking church in Paris, lovely welcome
Fantastic community is Godly people. If you are English speaking and in town, pop by and visit.
It's a family friendly congregation and I easily felt at home
A beautiful place to worship God ! Super community
English speaking church in the heart of Paris with a friendly atmosphere.
Blessed church, blessed pastors and lovely people
A beautiful place filled with beautiful souls ! A warm welcoming team
Visited with my wife whilst on holiday. Very friendly.
Anglican Church in the heart of Paris with a big heart for Christ.

Whether you are visiting Paris or looking for an English speaking church, stop by one of the three Sunday services at Saint Michael's. People are warm and welcoming and the sermons are interesting and thought provoking. There's a high church service at 9:30 am for people looking for a more liturgical experience. A 10:45 service (the one I usually go to) with a wonderful worship service, groups for children of all ages and a coffee and tea bar at the end of the service, ideal if you are new to Paris. There's also a new 6 pm service, with a Q & A session for those looking for more of a Bible study (wine and snacks are provided at the end). P.S. St. Michael's also has a lovely Tamil community that meets for service in Tamil at 4pm.
